author: Rob Taylor
title: Protectionism Concerns, North Korea Dominate Asean-Australia Summit
text:
SYDNEY—Southeast Asian leaders and Australia’s prime minister pledged to strengthen economic ties to confront the growing backlash against globalization and called on North Korea to end its nuclear and missile program.
Concluding a special summit aimed at binding Australia more closely to its neighbors amid China’s growing influence and uncertainty over the U.S.’s commitment to Asia, regional leaders also warned against rising protectionism, in what appeared to be a veiled criticism of the White House’s tariff plans.
